Diagnosis: dispatch=0 means the enricher workers were fine, but 100% of
drops were at the collector→enricher channel boundary. Root cause: the
enricher's single Run goroutine shared file/net/sweep handling AND the
process dispatcher in one select. When a file or net event triggered
inline /proc-backed enrichment, the main loop stalled, the cg.Process
channel filled, and the collector's non-blocking send dropped at the
ringbuf-drain boundary. Visible on RHEL 10 but not Debian 13 because
RHEL produced ~24k events/s vs Debian's ~12k/s on this workload.

Fix: run the process dispatcher in its own goroutine so file/net event
handling in the main select cannot block process dispatch. Shipped as
part of task #15 follow-up; load-test rerun pending.


