Successful throughput ceiling: ~6k events/s sustained on this VM.
Debian 13 in the same 4 vCPU / 4 GB configuration sustains ~12k/s
with identical code at <0.1% drops — the delta is inherent to this
RHEL 10 VM's CPU-per-goroutine allocation or kernel scheduling, not
any specific stage of our pipeline (cache contention, worker pool,
/proc reads, reflection, and goroutine-share-of-main-select have all
been systematically eliminated as bottlenecks).

Phase 1 functional criteria (loader loads, events emit, detection
